31
	COMP
		GE&E
	HURR
		ge_e (ge+e)
	FORM
		W[hvv{[0ddd]u[{0hh}vv2]ME}]
	NAME
		GE+E GE_E GE(E) GEE
	NOTE
		Like Hittite, Hurrian had five vowels and no voicing distinctions, so they had conventions to reduce ambiguity: GI/GE only for ge, KI/KE only for ki, KU only for ko, GU only for gu. Since this convention wasn't used in Hittite, sometimes ligatures like this were introduced to reduce ambiguity further.
