	NAME
		BAPPIR
	NOTE
		This "beer-bread" (more often just bappir) is a hard biscuit used for beer-making rather than eating. It contains all the key ingredients for beer in a form that's easy to store long-term, so it can be crumbled into malted water and fermented on demand.
