			their
		<EM-ṢÚ>
			sour
			rennet
	NOTE
		Strictly speaking, Akk <SU> and <SUNU> should only be used after a dental consonant, with <ŠU> and <ŠUNU> used elsewhere. Hittite scribes were not always consistent about this; some transcribers prefer to call it ZU rather than SÚ or ṢÚ, because the most likely explanation is that Hittite scribes just couldn't tell the difference between Akkadian S, Z, and Ṣ.
