		Hittite scribes regularly used an old form of ZU to write GÍN "shekel", so this sign is usually read as GÍN. However, the standard form of GÍN (#223) is also found in letters from Egypt. The HZL gives them both the reading GÍN, but assigns them different index numbers. For clarity, we assign the reading GIN₉ here for the peculiarly Hittite form, and reserve GÍN for the standard one.
