	AKK
		lì
		lim
		si₁₇
		še₂₀
		<LIM>
			thousand(?)
	SUM
		IGI
			eye, see
	FORM
		[cvh]
		[c'(vh)]	variant
		(h[0v{h0}])	variant
		[cv{hh}]	variant unusual
	NAME
		ŠI LÌ LI3 ŠE20 LIM SI17 IGI 1000
	NOTE
		The reading <lim> arose from a combination of U "ten" and <ME> "hundred" (Akk līmu "thousand"), only coincidentally similar to IGI "eye". <LIM> as a logogram for "thousand" is never found in Hittite sources, which prefer <LI-IM>, but we still give this sign the reading "1000" based on the Hittite use of LIM-gunu (#239) for "ten thousand" and LIM-gunu-šeššig (#336B) for "hundred thousand"
	LIG
		ši(-iš)
			abbreviation for šintaḫiš
		ši-zi, ši-la
			abbreviation for LÚ^šizišalla (LÚ^IGI-zišalla?)
		IGI-an-da
			across from, facing (menaḫḫanda)
		IGI-zi
			sees (aušzi, uškizzi)
			first, before (ḫantezzi-)
		IGI-zi-ya
			[type of official] (ḫantezziya-)
		IGI-u-en
			we saw (ušgawen)
		IGI-<UL>
			he looked (Akk iṭṭul)
