	COMP
		KI×MIN
	AKK
		<U₇>
			and
	FORM
		W[c{[v{hhhh}]Ah}v[vv]Mv]
	NAME
		KIMIN U₇
	NOTE
		Alteration of KI+MIN "ditto" used to mean "and" in some Akk texts from Hattusa; sometimes given the Sumerian name KIMIN based on its composition, other times named <U₇> from Akk <u> "and". Treated as a graphic ligature in the HZL and thus not given its own name or index number, but we consider it a sign rather than a ligature because the MIN is enclosed by the KI rather than standing side by side.
