326
	COMP
		wa+a
	HURR
		wa_a (wa₄)
		fa
	FORM
		[{cc}v{h[vv2]M}]
		[{cc}v{d[vv2]ME}]	variant
		[{cc}v(h[vv2]M)]	variant
	NAME
		WA+A WA_A WA(A) WAA FA WA4
	NOTE
		The signs combining WA with various vowels are used only in foreign (Hurrian, Hattic, Palaic) words, so they probably represent a non-Hittite sound. Hurrian scholars traditionally transcribe these with a <w> (with readings <wa_a>, <we_e>, <wi_i>, <wu_u>, <wu_ú>, the underscore representing a subscript; or <wa₄>, <wé>, <wí>, <wú>, <wù>), but since these signs are never used for the Hittite /w/, we prefer the readings <fa>, <fe>, <fi>, <fo>, <fu>. See <wa_ap> (#318) for discussion of the VC equivalents.
