336B
	COMP
		"GAŠAN+TI"
	SUM
		"GAŠAN+TI"
			100,000
	FORM
		L[{ddhuu}cvhc']	reconstructed
	NOTE
		This sign is never directly attested, but is reconstructed based on several places where a Neo-Hittite scribe seems to have corrected an Old Hittite sign for "hundred thousand" into the incongruous logogram GAŠAN-<TI> (Akk bēlti). Probably this isn't related to GAŠAN at all, but is a šeššig form of SIG₅ "ten thousand" (itself a gunu form of <LIM> "thousand", itself composed of U "ten" + <ME> "hundred"). The form here is taken from Hoffner's "On Higher Numbers in Hittite" and given the placeholder readings GAŠAN+TI and 100000.
	NAME
		GAŠAN+TI 100000
