	NOTE
		(1) The reading IŠKUR is not in the HZL, but like the distinction between UD "day" and UTU "sun god", a convention has arisen to use IM for "wind" and IŠKUR for "storm god". (2) Hoffner argues that IM.GAL is an error for the proper Sumerian IM.GÁL "south wind", but the HZL prefers a reading "great wind". Either way, IM.GÁL is not found in Hittite. (3) The translation "anointed" for GUDU₁₂ is conventional based on the Akkadian rendering, but the Hittite GUDU₁₂-priests (kumra-) don't seem to have had anything to do with anointing.
